---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="CSRF Configuration - Astro 6">
	<main>
		<a href="/" class="back-link">← Back to Home</a>
		
		<h1>CSRF Configuration Options</h1>
		
		<section>
			<h2>Default Behavior (Zero Config)</h2>
			<p>
				By default, Astro 6 enables CSRF protection for all state-changing requests:
			</p>
			<ul>
				<li>✅ <code>POST</code> requests</li>
				<li>✅ <code>PUT</code> requests</li>
				<li>✅ <code>PATCH</code> requests</li>
				<li>✅ <code>DELETE</code> requests</li>
			</ul>
			<p>
				<code>GET</code> requests are NOT protected (they should be idempotent anyway).
			</p>
		</section>
		
		<section>
			<h2>When Is It Active?</h2>
			<p>CSRF protection is enabled in:</p>
			<ul>
				<li>✅ Server-Side Rendering (SSR) mode</li>
				<li>✅ Hybrid mode (pages with <code>export const prerender = false</code>)</li>
			</ul>
			<p>Not needed in:</p>
			<ul>
				<li>❌ Static mode (no server = no session = no CSRF risk)</li>
				<li>❌ Client-only apps</li>
			</ul>
		</section>
		
		<section>
			<h2>Customizing CSRF Protection</h2>
			<p>Configure in <code>astro.config.mjs</code>:</p>
			
			<pre><code>// astro.config.mjs
export default defineConfig({
  output: 'server', // or 'hybrid'
  
  security: {
    csrf: {
      // Enable or disable CSRF protection
      enabled: true, // default: true
      
      // Customize token cookie name
      cookieName: '_csrf', // default: 'astro.csrf'
      
      // Customize token field name
      fieldName: 'csrf_token', // default: 'astro.csrf.token'
      
      // Paths to exclude from CSRF protection
      exclude: [
        '/api/public/*', // Public API endpoints
        '/webhooks/*',   // External webhooks
      ],
      
      // Custom error handler
      onInvalidToken: (request) => {
        return new Response('CSRF token invalid', { 
          status: 403,
          headers: { 'Content-Type': 'text/plain' }
        });
      },
    }
  }
});</code></pre>
		</section>
		
		<section>
			<h2>Excluding Specific Routes</h2>
			<p><strong>When to exclude:</strong></p>
			<ul>
				<li>Public API endpoints (authentication via API keys, not cookies)</li>
				<li>Webhook receivers (GitHub, Stripe, etc.)</li>
				<li>Third-party integrations</li>
			</ul>
			
			<p><strong>Example:</strong></p>
			<pre><code>security: {
  csrf: {
    exclude: [
      '/api/public/*',     // Public API
      '/webhook/stripe',   // Stripe webhooks
      '/webhook/github',   // GitHub webhooks
    ]
  }
}</code></pre>
			
			<div class="warning-box">
				<h3>⚠️ Security Warning</h3>
				<p>
					Only exclude routes that:
				</p>
				<ul>
					<li>Don't use cookie-based authentication</li>
					<li>Use alternative auth (API keys, signatures)</li>
					<li>Are truly public endpoints</li>
				</ul>
				<p>
					<strong>Never exclude user-facing forms or authenticated endpoints!</strong>
				</p>
			</div>
		</section>
		
		<section>
			<h2>Custom Token Validation</h2>
			<p>For advanced use cases, you can implement custom validation:</p>
			
			<pre><code>// src/middleware.js
export async function onRequest(context, next) {
  const { request } = context;
  
  if (request.method === 'POST') {
    // Access the CSRF token
    const token = request.headers.get('X-CSRF-Token');
    
    // Custom validation logic
    if (!isValidToken(token)) {
      return new Response('Invalid CSRF token', { status: 403 });
    }
  }
  
  return next();
}</code></pre>
		</section>
		
		<section>
			<h2>API Endpoints</h2>
			<p>CSRF protection works automatically with API routes:</p>
			
			<pre><code>// src/pages/api/transfer.ts
export async function POST({ request }) {
  // CSRF validation happens automatically
  // If we got here, the token was valid
  
  const data = await request.json();
  
  // Process the request safely
  return new Response(JSON.stringify({ success: true }), {
    headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' }
  });
}</code></pre>
			
			<p>For frontend requests to API endpoints:</p>
			<pre><code>// Get CSRF token from cookie
const csrfToken = getCookie('astro.csrf');

// Include in request header
fetch('/api/transfer', {
  method: 'POST',
  headers: {
    'Content-Type': 'application/json',
    'X-CSRF-Token': csrfToken
  },
  body: JSON.stringify({ amount: 100 })
});</code></pre>
		</section>
		
		<section>
			<h2>Testing CSRF Protection</h2>
			<p>Verify your protection works:</p>
			
			<div class="test-steps">
				<div class="test">
					<h3>✅ Test 1: Valid Request</h3>
					<ol>
						<li>Load the form page</li>
						<li>Submit the form normally</li>
						<li>Should succeed (token is valid)</li>
					</ol>
				</div>
				
				<div class="test">
					<h3>❌ Test 2: Missing Token</h3>
					<ol>
						<li>Use curl or Postman</li>
						<li>Send POST without token</li>
						<li>Should get 403 Forbidden</li>
					</ol>
					<pre><code>curl -X POST http://localhost:4321/transfer \
  -d "amount=100&email=test@example.com"
# Should return 403</code></pre>
				</div>
				
				<div class="test">
					<h3>❌ Test 3: Invalid Token</h3>
					<ol>
						<li>Load the form</li>
						<li>Edit token value in DevTools</li>
						<li>Submit form</li>
						<li>Should get 403 Forbidden</li>
					</ol>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>
		
		<section>
			<h2>Best Practices</h2>
			<ul>
				<li>✅ Keep CSRF protection enabled (it's on by default)</li>
				<li>✅ Use HTTPS in production (prevents token theft)</li>
				<li>✅ Set <code>SameSite=Lax</code> or <code>Strict</code> on cookies</li>
				<li>✅ Validate token server-side (Astro does this)</li>
				<li>✅ Use short token lifetimes</li>
				<li>✅ Regenerate tokens after login</li>
				<li>❌ Don't disable CSRF for authenticated routes</li>
				<li>❌ Don't expose tokens in URLs</li>
				<li>❌ Don't trust client-side validation only</li>
			</ul>
		</section>
		
		<section>
			<h2>Troubleshooting</h2>
			
			<div class="troubleshoot">
				<h3>Problem: Getting 403 on legitimate requests</h3>
				<p><strong>Causes:</strong></p>
				<ul>
					<li>Token cookie not being set (check cookies in DevTools)</li>
					<li>Form missing token field (inspect HTML)</li>
					<li>Cookie domain mismatch</li>
					<li>SameSite cookie settings too strict</li>
				</ul>
				<p><strong>Solutions:</strong></p>
				<ul>
					<li>Verify cookies are enabled</li>
					<li>Check browser console for errors</li>
					<li>Ensure proper cookie configuration</li>
				</ul>
			</div>
			
			<div class="troubleshoot">
				<h3>Problem: Token not in form</h3>
				<p><strong>Check:</strong></p>
				<ul>
					<li>Using SSR or hybrid mode (not static)</li>
					<li>Form uses <code>method="POST"</code></li>
					<li>Astro version is 6.0 or higher</li>
				</ul>
			</div>
		</section>
	</main>
</Layout>

<style>
	main {
		max-width: 900px;
		margin: 0 auto;
		padding: 2rem;
	}
	
	.back-link {
		display: inline-block;
		margin-bottom: 2rem;
		color: #0066cc;
		text-decoration: none;
	}
	
	section {
		margin: 3rem 0;
		padding: 2rem;
		background: #f9f9f9;
		border-radius: 0.5rem;
	}
	
	h1 {
		font-size: 2.5rem;
		margin-bottom: 2rem;
	}
	
	h2 {
		font-size: 1.5rem;
		margin-bottom: 1rem;
		color: #555;
	}
	
	h3 {
		font-size: 1.25rem;
		margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
	}
	
	code {
		background: #ffe7e7;
		padding: 0.2rem 0.4rem;
		border-radius: 0.25rem;
		font-family: 'Courier New', monospace;
		font-size: 0.9em;
	}
	
	pre {
		background: #2d2d2d;
		color: #f8f8f2;
		padding: 1.5rem;
		border-radius: 0.5rem;
		overflow-x: auto;
		font-size: 0.875rem;
		line-height: 1.5;
		margin: 1rem 0;
	}
	
	pre code {
		background: none;
		padding: 0;
		color: inherit;
	}
	
	ul, ol {
		line-height: 1.8;
	}
	
	li {
		margin: 0.5rem 0;
	}
	
	.warning-box {
		background: #fff3cd;
		border-left: 4px solid #ffc107;
		padding: 1.5rem;
		margin: 1.5rem 0;
	}
	
	.warning-box h3 {
		margin-top: 0;
		color: #856404;
	}
	
	.test-steps {
		display: grid;
		gap: 1.5rem;
		margin-top: 1.5rem;
	}
	
	.test {
		background: white;
		padding: 1.5rem;
		border-radius: 0.5rem;
		border: 1px solid #ddd;
	}
	
	.test h3 {
		margin-top: 0;
	}
	
	.troubleshoot {
		background: white;
		padding: 1.5rem;
		border-radius: 0.5rem;
		margin: 1.5rem 0;
		border-left: 4px solid #0066cc;
	}
	
	.troubleshoot h3 {
		margin-top: 0;
		color: #0066cc;
	}
</style>
